In [[mathematics]], an '''Igusa curve''' is (roughly) a coarse [[moduli space]] of [[elliptic curve]]s in characteristic ''p'' with a level ''p'' Igusa structure, where an '''Igusa structure''' on an elliptic curve ''E'' is roughly a point of order ''p'' of ''E''<sup>(''p'')</sup> generating the kernel of ''V'':''E''<sup>(''p'')</sup>&nbsp;→&nbsp;''E''.  An '''Igusa variety''' is a higher-dimensional analogue of an Igusa curve. Igusa curves were studied by {{harvs|txt|last=Igusa|authorlink=Jun-Ichi Igusa|year=1968}} and Igusa varieties were introduced by {{harvtxt|Harris|Taylor|2001}}.

